The paper deals with source coding with side information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses distortion measures and reconstruction sequences, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions discrete memoryless sources and joint laws, which are concepts in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides a solution for a more general problem involving multiple distortion constraints, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
